<section id="research" class="page-section section-alt">
  <div class="page-wrap">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Research</h2>
    <p class="section-intro" style="margin-top:16px;">My research focuses on one central challenge: how do we monitor biodiversity at the scale and speed that forest management decisions actually require? My projects span the Amazon, Atlantic Forest, Borneo, and the U.S. Southeast — generating data that is rigorous, scalable, and actionable.</p>

    <div class="research-grid">
      <div class="research-card">
        <span class="location-badge">📍 Peruvian Amazon · Ongoing</span>
        <h3>Impacts of Liana Cutting on Tropical Forest Biodiversity</h3>
        <p>In collaboration with Conservation International, using a staggered BACI design with bioacoustics and camera traps to assess how wildlife responds to liana cutting — a proposed tool for enhancing carbon sequestration in selectively logged tropical forests.</p>
        <span class="tag-pill">Bioacoustics</span><span class="tag-pill">Camera Trapping</span><span class="tag-pill">BACI Design</span><span class="tag-pill">Carbon</span>
      </div>

      <div class="research-card">
        <img src="images/borneo-monkeys.jpg" class="research-card-img" alt="Proboscis monkeys at dusk, Borneo">
        <span class="location-badge">📍 Global · Multi-site · Ongoing</span>
        <h3>Soundscape Baseline Project</h3>
        <p>Establishing biodiversity baselines in some of the world's most intact forests using soundscapes, camera traps, and machine learning — with open, scalable protocols for evidence-based conservation worldwide.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://soundforestlab.org/soundscapebaselines" target="_blank">soundforestlab.org/soundscapebaselines</a></p>
        <span class="tag-pill">Passive Acoustic Monitoring</span><span class="tag-pill">Machine Learning</span><span class="tag-pill">Remote Sensing</span>
      </div>

      <div class="research-card">
        <span class="location-badge">📍 Caazapá, Paraguay · Atlantic Forest</span>
        <h3>Soundscapes of the Tapytá Natural Reserve</h3>
        <p>Mapping biodiversity across the fragmented Atlantic Forest of Paraguay using passive acoustic monitoring and AI — forests, grasslands, and eucalyptus plantations. Led with the Moisés Bertoni Foundation.</p>
        <span class="tag-pill">Atlantic Forest</span><span class="tag-pill">Soundscape Indices</span><span class="tag-pill">Paraguay</span>
      </div>

      <div class="research-card">
        <span class="location-badge">📍 Southeastern U.S. Coastal Plain · PhD Research</span>
        <h3>Winter Foraging Ecology of Bats in Working Forests</h3>
        <p>Integrating bioacoustics, trapping, insect light trapping, advanced modeling, and DNA metabarcoding to understand bat winter ecology and their role as pest controllers in working forests.</p>
        <span class="tag-pill">Bat Ecology</span><span class="tag-pill">White-Nose Syndrome</span><span class="tag-pill">DNA Metabarcoding</span><span class="tag-pill">Occupancy Modeling</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

